@p
  Scalafix is a new tool to help Scala 2.x code compile with @dotty(),
  a next generation compiler for Scala.

@p
  The project is still in the early days of development, so there is not much
  to see here yet.
  Currently, a lot of work on scalafix happens in
  @lnk("scala.meta", "http://scalameta.org"),
  the metaprogramming toolkit that powers the scalafix @sect.ref{Rewrites}.

@p
  Fun fact. The name "scalafix" is inspired by
  @lnk("gofix", "https://golang.org/cmd/fix/"),
  a similar tool used to migrate go code.

